Cody pressed on. His hands were beginning to sweat, so he wiped them on his shirt, carefully taking them off the haft of
the pole sickle one at a time. “Not entirely appropriate garb for this kind of work,” he said absently. “Although I suppose
it's just another kind of travel and exploration. Cody Zissou, freelance tourist.” He chuckled at that, then immediately
fell silent, looking about suspiciously.
